import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', bins=50, kde=True, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['delay'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['origin'] = data['origin'].astype('category')
    data['destination'] = data['destination'].astype('category')

    average_delay = data.groupby('origin')['delay'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='origin', y='delay', data=average_delay, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the average delay time for flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Airline')
    plt.ylabel('Average Delay Time (minutes)')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Airline', loc='upper right', labels=average_delay['origin'].unique())

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    total_delays = data.groupby('origin')['delay'].sum().reset_index()
    total_delays = total_delays.sort_values(by='delay', ascending=False)
    
    chart = sns.barplot(x='origin', y='delay', data=total_delays)
    plt.title('Which airports have the most delays?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Airport')
    plt.ylabel('Total Delay Time (minutes)')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['date'] = data['date'].dt.date

    daily_flights = data.groupby('date').size().reset_index(name='num_flights')
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(data=daily_flights, x='date', y='num_flights')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight dates?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
